Questions.correct_ans_explanation:
Since this sequentialSearch method is recursive, we need to know when to stop this recursion. One way this recursion ends is if target is found in data and the index is returned. But what if this target value is not found? Then last will keep decreasing and eventually be less than 0. To avoid this IndexOutOfBoundsException, we must place a condition that returns -1 if last is less than 0. It will look like this:

    if (last < 0)               
        return -1;

Questions.wrong_ans_explanation:
