Questions.correct_ans_explanation:
The statement

    double r = Math.random();

produces a random real number in the range 0.0 to 1.0 such that 0.0 ≤ r < 1.0. This range can be scaled and shifted.

In general, to produce a random real value in the range lowValue ≤ x < highValue:

double x = (highValue - lowValue) * Math.random() + lowValue;

