Questions.correct_ans_explanation:
Declaration I works because there is a default constructor in the PosInt class. The reason declaration II works is that, because the superclass PosInt has a default constructor, the following code will automatically be placed in the subclass EvenPosInt:

    public EvenPosInt()
    { super(); }    //calls default constructor from superclass

This only works for a default constructor. So declaration III fails because superclass constructors are not inherited. You need to add the following constructor code to EvenPosInt to make declaration III work:

    public EvenPosInt(int aValue)
    { super(aValue); }

